 Lih</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="contentSub"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">\n\t\t\t\t\tJump to:\t\t\t\t\t<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, \t\t\t\t\t<a href="#p-search">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><table class="infobox biography vcard" style="width:22em">\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold"><span class="fn">Andrew Lih</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:WikiConference_USA_2015_90.JPG" class="image"><img alt="WikiConference USA 2015 90.JPG" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/WikiConference_USA_2015_90.JPG/220px-WikiConference_USA_2015_90.JPG" width="220" height="327" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/WikiConference_USA_2015_90.JPG/330px-WikiConference_USA_2015_90.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/WikiConference_USA_2015_90.JPG/440px-WikiConference_USA_2015_90.JPG 2x" data-file-width="1982" data-file-height="2949" /></a>\n<div>Lih speaking at the <a href="/wiki/National_Archives_and_Records_Administration" title="National Archives and Records Administration">National Archives and Records Administration</a> in 2015</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row">Native&#160;name</th>\n<td><span class="nickname">(<a href="/wiki/Simplified_Chinese_characters" title="Simplified Chinese characters">simplified Chinese</a>: <span lang="zh-Hans">\xe9\x83\xa6\xe5\xae\x89\xe6\xb2\xbb</span>; <a href="/wiki/Traditional_Chinese_characters" title="Traditional Chinese characters">traditional Chinese</a>: <span lang="zh-Hant">\xe9\x85\x88\xe5\xae\x89\xe6\xb2\xbb</span>; <a href="/wiki/Pinyin" title="Pinyin">pinyin</a>: <i><span lang="zh-Latn-pinyin">L\xc3\xac \xc4\x80nzh\xc3\xac</span></i>)<sup id="cite_ref-hku_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-hku-1">[1]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row">Born</th>\n<td>1968 (age&#160;48\xe2\x80\x9349)<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row">Residence</th>\n<td class="label"><a href="/wiki/Washington,_District_of_Columbia" class="mw-redirect" title="Washington, District of Columbia">Washington, District of Columbia</a>, <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row">Nationality</th>\n<td class="category">American</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row">Other&#160;names</th>\n<td class="nickname">Fuzheado<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row">Alma&#160;mater</th>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Columbia_University" title="Columbia University">Columbia University</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row">Occupation</th>\n<td class="role">Scientist and professor</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row">Known&#160;for</th>\n<td>studying various open technology cultures, such as Wikipedia and wikimedia</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th scope="row">Website</th>\n<td><span class="url"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://andrewlih.com/">andrewlih<wbr />.com</a></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center">\n<table role="presentation" class="mbox-small" style="background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000;border-collapse:collapse; border-width:1px 0 0 0; background:transparent; float:none; margin:0 -5px">\n<tr>\n<td style="width:1px"></td>\n<td class="mbox-text plainlist" style="line-height:1.1em">\n<div class="haudio">\n<div style="padding:4px 0"><a href="/wiki/File:Andrew_Lih_voice.flac" title="File:Andrew Lih voice.flac">Lih\'s voice</a></div>\n<div>\n<div class="mediaContainer" style="width:220px"><audio id="mwe_player_0" controls="" preload="none" style="width:220px" class="kskin" data-durationhint="14.103375" data-startoffset="0" data-mwtitle="Andrew_Lih_voice.flac" data-mwprovider="wikimediacommons">\n<source src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/f/fa/Andrew_Lih_voice.flac/Andrew_Lih_voice.flac.ogg" type="audio/ogg; codecs=&quot;vorbis&quot;" data-title="Ogg Vorbis" data-shorttitle="Ogg Vorbis" data-transcodekey="ogg" data-width="0" data-height="0" data-bandwidth="129120" />\n<source src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fa/Andrew_Lih_voice.flac" type="audio/flac" data-title="Original FLAC file (1.2 Mbps)" data-shorttitle="FLAC source" data-width="0" data-height="0" data-bandwidth="1199691" /></audio></div>\n</div>\n<div class="description" style="padding:2px 0 0 0">recorded May 2017</div>\n</div>\n<hr /></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p><b>Andrew Lih</b> (<a href="/wiki/Simplified_Chinese_characters" title="Simplified Chinese characters">simplified Chinese</a>: <span lang="zh-Hans">\xe9\x83\xa6\xe5\xae\x89\xe6\xb2\xbb</span>; <a href="/wiki/Traditional_Chinese_characters" title="Traditional Chinese characters">traditional Chinese</a>: <span lang="zh-Hant">\xe9\x85\x88\xe5\xae\x89\xe6\xb2\xbb</span>; <a href="/wiki/Pinyin" title="Pinyin">pinyin</a>: <i><span lang="zh-Latn-pinyin">L\xc3\xac \xc4\x80nzh\xc3\xac</span></i>; born 1968) is an American <a href="/wiki/New_media" title="New media">new media</a> researcher, consultant and writer, as well as an authority on both <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia" title="Wikipedia">Wikipedia</a> and <a href="/wiki/Internet_censorship_in_the_People%27s_Republic_of_China" class="mw-redirect" title="Internet censorship in the People\'s Republic of China">internet censorship in the People\'s Republic of China</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup> He is currently an associate professor of journalism at <a href="/wiki/American_University" title="American University">American University</a> in Washington, D.C.<sup id="cite_ref-10" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-10">[10]</a></sup></p>\n<p></p>\n<div id="toc" class="toc">\n<div class="toctitle">\n<h2>Contents</h2>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Life_and_career"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Life and career</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="#Wikipedia_activity"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Wikipedia activity</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-3"><a href="#Selected_publications"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">Selected publications</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-4"><a href="#References"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">References</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-5"><a href="#External_links"><span class="tocnumber">5</span> <span class="toctext">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Life_and_career">Life and career</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Lih&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Life and career">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="thumb tleft">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:172px;"><a href="/wiki/File:2014_WikiConference_USA_(Group_H)_14.JPG" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/63/2014_WikiConference_USA_%28Group_H%29_14.JPG/170px-2014_WikiConference_USA_%28Group_H%29_14.JPG" width="170" height="256" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/63/2014_WikiConference_USA_%28Group_H%29_14.JPG/255px-2014_WikiConference_USA_%28Group_H%29_14.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/63/2014_WikiConference_USA_%28Group_H%29_14.JPG/340px-2014_WikiConference_USA_%28Group_H%29_14.JPG 2x" data-file-width="3264" data-file-height="4912" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:2014_WikiConference_USA_(Group_H)_14.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nLih speaking at WikiConference USA in 2014</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<table class="infobox" style="width:22em;width: 210px; float: right; clear: right; margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em">\n<caption>External video</caption>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:Andrew_Lih.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Andrew Lih.jpg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b8/Andrew_Lih.jpg/210px-Andrew_Lih.jpg" width="210" height="141" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b8/Andrew_Lih.jpg/315px-Andrew_Lih.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b8/Andrew_Lih.jpg/420px-Andrew_Lih.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3916" data-file-height="2634" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center;text-align: left"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/16px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png" width="16" height="16" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/24px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/32px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="128" data-file-height="128" /> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p2MEGk5q1WI">How Wikipedia solved the knowledge gap, Andrew Lih, TEDxAmericanUniversity</a>, <a href="/wiki/TED_(conference)" title="TED (conference)">TEDx</a>, 17:19<sup id="cite_ref-TEDx_11-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-TEDx-11">[11]</a></sup></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>Lih worked as a software engineer for <a href="/wiki/AT%26T_Bell_Labs" class="mw-redirect" title="AT&amp;T Bell Labs">AT&amp;T Bell Labs</a> from 1990 to 1993. He founded the new-media startup Mediabridge Infosystems in 1994. He also obtained a <a href="/wiki/Masters_degree" class="mw-redirect" title="Masters degree">Masters degree</a> in <a href="/wiki/Computer_Science" class="mw-redirect" title="Computer Science">Computer Science</a> from <a href="/wiki/Columbia_University" title="Columbia University">Columbia University</a> in 1994.<sup id="cite_ref-cv_12-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-cv-12">[12]</a></sup></p>\n<p>From 1995 to 2000 he served as an <a href="/wiki/Adjunct_professor" title="Adjunct professor">adjunct professor</a> of journalism at Columbia, and director of technology for their Center for New Media.<sup id="cite_ref-13" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-13">[13]</a></sup> In 2000 he formed Columbia\'s Interactive Design Lab, a collaboration with the university\'s School of the Arts to explore interactive design for both fiction and non-fiction, including advertising, news, documentaries and films.<sup id="cite_ref-hku_1-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-hku-1">[1]</a></sup> Soon afterward, Lih served as an <a href="/wiki/Assistant_professor" title="Assistant professor">assistant professor</a> and the Director of Technology at the Journalism and Media Studies Centre of the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Hong_Kong" title="University of Hong Kong">University of Hong Kong</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-hku_1-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-hku-1">[1]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-atlantic_14-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-atlantic-14">[14]</a></sup></p>\n<p>He then moved to <a href="/wiki/Beijing" title="Beijing">Beijing</a>, <a href="/wiki/People%27s_Republic_of_China" class="mw-redirect" title="People\'s Republic of China">China</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-atlantic_14-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-atlantic-14">[14]</a></sup> where he lived until 2009. He currently lives in Washington, D.C., where he is an associate professor at <a href="/wiki/American_University" title="American University">American University</a>\'s <a href="/wiki/American_University_School_of_Communication" title="American University School of Communication">School of Communication</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-15" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-15">[15]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Wikipedia_activity">Wikipedia activity</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Lih&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Wikipedia activity">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:201px;">\n<div id="mwe_player_1" class="PopUpMediaTransform" style="width:199px;" videopayload="&lt;div class=&quot;mediaContainer&quot; style=&quot;width:854px&quot;&gt;&lt;video id=&quot;mwe_player_2&quot; poster=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/2014-08_Andrew_Lih_at_Wikimania.webm/854px--2014-08_Andrew_Lih_at_Wikimania.webm.jpg&quot; controls=&quot;&quot; preload=&quot;none&quot; autoplay=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;width:854px;height:480px&quot; class=&quot;kskin&quot; data-durationhint=&quot;1134.008&quot; data-startoffset=&quot;0&quot; data-mwtitle=&quot;2014-08_Andrew_Lih_at_Wikimania.webm&quot; data-mwprovider=&quot;wikimediacommons&quot;&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/1/19/2014-08_Andrew_Lih_at_Wikimania.webm/2014-08_Andrew_Lih_at_Wikimania.webm.480p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;SD WebM (480P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 480P&quot; data-t