&quot;/&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&lt;/div&gt;"><img alt="File:2014-08 Andrew Lih at Wikimania.webm" style="width:199px;height:112px" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/2014-08_Andrew_Lih_at_Wikimania.webm/199px--2014-08_Andrew_Lih_at_Wikimania.webm.jpg" /><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/19/2014-08_Andrew_Lih_at_Wikimania.webm" title="Play media" target="new"><span class="play-btn-large"><span class="mw-tmh-playtext">Play media</span></span></a></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:2014-08_Andrew_Lih_at_Wikimania.webm" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\n2014-08 Andrew Lih at Wikimania</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>Lih is a veteran <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia" title="Wikipedia">Wikipedia</a> contributor and administrator on the English Wikipedia under the username <b>Fuzheado</b>.<sup id="cite_ref-16" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-16">[16]</a></sup> In 2009, he published the book <i><a href="/wiki/The_Wikipedia_Revolution" title="The Wikipedia Revolution">The Wikipedia Revolution: How a Bunch of Nobodies Created the World\'s Greatest Encyclopedia</a></i>. Lih has been interviewed in a variety of publications, including <i><a href="/wiki/Salon.com" class="mw-redirect" title="Salon.com">Salon.com</a></i>, <sup id="cite_ref-17" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-17">[17]</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/The_New_York_Times" title="The New York Times">The New York Times</a></i> <a href="/wiki/Freakonomics" title="Freakonomics">Freakonomics</a> blog,<sup id="cite_ref-18" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-18">[18]</a></sup> and <a href="/wiki/NPR" title="NPR">NPR</a> <a href="/wiki/Talk_of_the_Nation" title="Talk of the Nation">Talk of the Nation</a> <sup id="cite_ref-19" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-19">[19]</a></sup> as an expert on Wikipedia.</p>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;">\n<div id="mwe_player_3" class="PopUpMediaTransform" style="width:200px;" videopayload="&lt;div class=&quot;mediaContainer&quot; style=&quot;width:640px&quot;&gt;&lt;video id=&quot;mwe_player_4&quot; poster=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm/640px--Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm.jpg&quot; controls=&quot;&quot; preload=&quot;none&quot; autoplay=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;width:640px;height:360px&quot; class=&quot;kskin&quot; data-durationhint=&quot;5276.654&quot; data-startoffset=&quot;0&quot; data-mwtitle=&quot;Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia\'s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm&quot; data-mwprovider=&quot;wikimediacommons&quot;&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/95/Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Original WebM file, 640 \xc3\x97 360 (218 kbps)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM source&quot; data-width=&quot;640&quot; data-height=&quot;360&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;218038&quot; data-framerate=&quot;29.97&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/9/95/Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm/Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm.360p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;WebM (360P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 360P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;360p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;640&quot; data-height=&quot;360&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;427584&quot; data-framerate=&quot;29.97&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/9/95/Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm/Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm.160p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Low bandwidth WebM (160P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 160P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;160p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;284&quot; data-height=&quot;160&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;203304&quot; data-framerate=&quot;29.97&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/9/95/Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm/Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm.240p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Small WebM (240P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 240P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;240p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;426&quot; data-height=&quot;240&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;317496&quot; data-framerate=&quot;29.97&quot;/&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&lt;/div&gt;"><img alt="File:Wikimania 2014 - We Need to Talk about Paid Editing- Sorting Out Wikipedia\'s Most Enduring Argument-SD.webm" style="width:200px;height:113px" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm/200px--Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm.jpg" /><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/95/Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm" title="Play media" target="new"><span class="play-btn-large"><span class="mw-tmh-playtext">Play media</span></span></a></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Wikimania_2014_-_We_Need_to_Talk_about_Paid_Editing-_Sorting_Out_Wikipedia%27s_Most_Enduring_Argument-SD.webm" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nLih in 2014 speaking about paid advocacy editing on Wikipedia</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>Lih claims that editing Wikipedia with <a href="/wiki/Smartphone" title="Smartphone">smartphones</a> is difficult and this discourages new potential contributors. Lih claims several years running the number of Wikipedia editors has been falling and alleges there is serious disagreement among existing contributors how to resolve this. Lih fears these situations could imperil Wikipedia\xe2\x80\x99s long term future.<sup id="cite_ref-20" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-20">[20]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_publications">Selected publications</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Lih&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Selected publications">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><cite class="citation book">Lih, Andrew (2009). <i><a href="/wiki/The_Wikipedia_Revolution" title="The Wikipedia Revolution">The Wikipedia Revolution</a></i>. New York: <a href="/wiki/Hyperion_(publisher)" class="mw-redirect" title="Hyperion (publisher)">Hyperion</a>. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-4013-0371-4" title="Special:BookSources/1-4013-0371-4">1-4013-0371-4</a>. <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/232977686">232977686</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrew+Lih&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrew&amp;rft.aulast=Lih&amp;rft.btitle=The+Wikipedia+Revolution&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=1-4013-0371-4&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Hyperion&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F232977686&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Lih&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: References">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist columns references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-hku-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-hku_1-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-hku_1-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-hku_1-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">"<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20110718015354/http://jmsc.hku.hk/faculty/alih/">Andrew Lih</a>." <a href="/wiki/University_of_Hong_Kong" title="University of Hong Kong">University of Hong Kong</a>. Retrieved on February 28, 2012.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.andrewlih.com/about/">About</a>." Andrew Lih Official Website. Retrieved on February 28, 2012.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://annenberg.usc.edu/~/media/Faculty/CV/Lih_CV2009.ashx">Andrew Lih\'s academic CV</a></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a class="external free" href="https://meta.m.